This paper deals with the problem of weakly supervised learning, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The paper also discusses the statistical and computational tradeoffs in this problem, which suggests that it could be relevant to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and information theory (cs.IT). Among these categories, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories as they are directly related to the problem of weakly supervised learning. The paper's focus on computational efficiency also suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DS, while the information-theoretic analysis could make it relevant to cs.IT. Finally, the mention of image classification in the abstract suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.CV.
